Any attempt to portray the life of <185>a<209>kara runs into two genuine ç
difficulties. Firstly, the available material is too meagre to fix ç
his date. Secondly, the traditional biographies (all in Sanskrit) ç
are so full of miracles attributed to him that it is difficult to ç
accept them or explain them in any logical way.
Though almost all biographies agree that <185>a<209>kara lived just ç
for 32 years, the year of his birth varies from 508 <MS>B.<|>C.<D> ç
up to <MS>A.<|>D. <D>788. The most widely accepted year is <MS>A.<|>D.<D> ç
788. However some scholars push it back to <MS>A.<|>D.<D>684 also.
About 21 works that generally go by the name <185>a<209>karavijaya ç
or <185>a<209>kara- digvijaya dealing with <185>a<209>kara's life ç
